                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.926,
                                "byte_start": 105472,
                                "byte_stop": 153224,
                                "text": "This case concerns California\u0027s time limitation on applications for postconviction relief."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 11.926,
                                "stop": 34.332,
                                "byte_start": 153224,
                                "byte_stop": 242876,
                                "text": "The question presented: \u201cDoes California\u0027s requirement that habeas corpus petitions be filed as promptly as possible qualify as an independent State ground for denying relief adequate to bar a subsequent application for the same relief in federal court?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 34.332,
                                "stop": 46.954,
                                "byte_start": 242876,
                                "byte_stop": 293345,
                                "text": "Unlike most states, California does not employ fixed statutory deadlines to determine the timeliness of a state prisoner\u0027s petition for habeas corpus."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.954,
                                "stop": 53.931,
                                "byte_start": 293345,
                                "byte_stop": 321243,
                                "text": "Instead, California directs petitioners to file known claims without substantial delay."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.931,
                                "stop": 66.404,
                                "byte_start": 321243,
                                "byte_stop": 371190,
                                "text": "Petitioners are further instructed to state when they first learned of the claims they are asserting and to explain why they did not advance those claims sooner."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.404,
                                "stop": 75.01,
                                "byte_start": 371190,
                                "byte_stop": 405567,
                                "text": "Claims not presented as promptly as the circumstances allow may be denied as untimely."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.01,
                                "stop": 88.99,
                                "byte_start": 405567,
                                "byte_stop": 461469,
                                "text": "California courts signal that a habeas petition is denied as time barred by citing the California Supreme Court\u0027s controlling decisions, In re Clark and In re Robbins."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.99,
                                "stop": 95.341,
                                "byte_start": 461469,
                                "byte_stop": 486860,
                                "text": "But denial of a petition for undue delay is a may, not a must."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.341,
                                "stop": 106.601,
                                "byte_start": 486860,
                                "byte_stop": 531895,
                                "text": "A California court has discretion to pass over the question whether a petition was filed too late and simply deny the petition for want of merit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 106.601,
                                "stop": 128.05,
                                "byte_start": 531895,
                                "byte_stop": 617681,
                                "text": "Petitioner below, respondent here, Charles W. Martin presented claims for postconviction relief, allegations that his counsel had provided ineffective assistance in a habeas petition filed in the California Supreme Court, nearly five years after his conviction became final."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.05,
                                "stop": 134.289,
                                "byte_start": 617681,
                                "byte_stop": 642654,
                                "text": "Habeas petitioners in California can file directly in the Supreme Court."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.289,
                                "stop": 138.215,
                                "byte_start": 642654,
                                "byte_stop": 658432,
                                "text": "They need not climb up the judicial ladder to get there."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 138.215,
                                "stop": 145.066,
                                "byte_start": 658432,
                                "byte_stop": 685808,
                                "text": "Martin gave no reason for the long delay in asserting the ineffective assistance claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 145.066,
                                "stop": 149.565,
                                "byte_start": 685808,
                                "byte_stop": 703781,
                                "text": "Citing Clark and Robbins, the court denied Martin\u0027s petition."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 149.565,
                                "stop": 157.433,
                                "byte_start": 703781,
                                "byte_stop": 735232,
                                "text": "In turn, the Federal District Court dismissed Martin\u0027s Federal habeas petition raising the same claims."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.433,
                                "stop": 168.204,
                                "byte_start": 735232,
                                "byte_stop": 778386,
                                "text": "Denial of Martin\u0027s state court petition as untimely the District Court held rested on an adequate and independent state procedural ground."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.204,
                                "stop": 194.222,
                                "byte_start": 778386,
                                "byte_stop": 882458,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit reversed.Contrasting the precision -- precision of fixed statutory deadlines, for example one year but California\u0027s no substantial delay formulation a Federal Appeals Court held that California\u0027s standard lacked the clarity and certainty necessary to constitute an adequate state bar."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 194.222,
                                "stop": 197.302,
                                "byte_start": 882458,
                                "byte_stop": 894683,
                                "text": "We reversed that judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 197.302,
                                "stop": 223.422,
                                "byte_start": 894683,
                                "byte_stop": 999173,
                                "text": "In a 2009 decision, Beard -- Beard against Kindler, this Court clarified that a state procedural bar may qualify as an adequate and independent state ground for denying a federal habeas petition even if the state court had discretion to omit ruling on the procedural barrier and instead ruled on the merits."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 223.422,
                                "stop": 251.062,
                                "byte_start": 999173,
                                "byte_stop": 1109723,
                                "text": "Guided by that decision, we hold that California is not put to the choice of imposing a specific deadline for habeas petitions which would almost certainly rule out Martin\u0027s nearly five-year delay or preserving the flexibility of it\u0027s current practice but at a considerable price, opening the door to federal habeas review and thereby undermining the finality of state court judgments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 251.062,
                                "stop": 264.423,
                                "byte_start": 1109723,
                                "byte_stop": 1163222,
                                "text": "In ruling for California, we stress that Martin has not alleged that the state\u0027s time bar, either by design or in operation, discriminates against federal claims or claimants."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 264.423,
                                "stop": 266.658,
                                "byte_start": 1163222,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The opinion of the court is unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
